Sorry to burst your bubble. ;) It happens to most of us, though. I have a
Jake--he's never been in a class or a baseball team without another Jake. I
have a John--well, we knew going in there would be plenty of those. (To be
more unique, he dropped the H from his name--now he's just like all the
Jonathan's!) And I have a Will--and while it's not as popular as Jake was, they're
popping up all over the place, too. Shoulda called him Billy--then he'd only
have to compete with his female cousin!

Tuck

messages.messageBody:
Well, her names are creative anyway!!
We have a furry little girl here named Luna, that was my favorite on her list
of course.
Luna is a rattie, black with white markings and oh-so-sweet.

I had started a childrens story with a character named Periwinkle. I'm not
sure I like her "booger" name though. :)

Sierra's middle name is Star. I like Azia, Connor, Donovan too.
My dh liked Biff, Turk and Astra. Hmmmmm....
I think he has issues.

Ren
